}
```

> **Hue:** Color angle (0 = red, 120 = green, 240 = blue)  
> **Saturation:** Intensity of color (0% = gray, 100% = full color)  
> **Lightness:** Brightness (0% = black, 50% = normal, 100% = white)

## Conclusion

Using different color formats in CSS provides flexibility and precision in design. ðŸŽ¨

