## Understand CSS Grid: Two-Dimensional Layout Control ðŸŽ¨

## Introduction

CSS Grid is a powerful layout system designed to handle both **rows** and **columns**. Unlike Flexbox (which is one-dimensional), Grid provides complete two-dimensional control, making it perfect for complex web layouts.

---

## 1. Defining a Grid Container ðŸ“¦

Start by declaring a container as a grid using `display: grid;`.

```css
.container {
  display: grid;
}
```

---

## 2. Setting Rows and Columns ðŸ“

Use `grid-template-rows` and `grid-template-columns` to define the number and size of rows and columns.

```css
.container {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 100px 200px;
  grid-template-rows: 150px 150px;
}
```

